rComments: He's a really nice man and very helpful. Quizzes were pretty easy, that is if you do the homework along with the class. But his exams were pretty hard. A lot of hard work is required for this class, but as long as you attend the lectures and do the homework, you'll be perfectly fine.

He is a nice guy. Helps you out if you need it, especially in office hours.  However, his lectures are terrible.  They are all over the place.  He gets lost in his examples and seems to always make mistakes which throws off the flow of the class.  HIs tests are doable but this class is rough.
